nodes.bodyText:
In my opinion

It would be noisy to leave a warn message every time.
It is not efficient to convert RetryRule to RetryRuleWithContent everytime.

How about adding a package-private method to RetryConfig such as
class RetryConfig {
	RetryRuleWithContent<T> fromRetryRule() {
	    if (fromRetryRule == null) {
	      logger.warn("...")
	      fromRetryRule = RetryRuleUtil.fromRetryRule(retryConfig.retryRule());
	    }
	    return fromRetryRule;
	}
}

